cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.SI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses traffic control schemes and bandwidth allocation in shared access networks, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper mentions quality of service (QoS) which is related to security and cryptography in network communication. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the allocation of excess bandwidth among active subscribers proportional to their token generation rates, which involves information theory concepts. 
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper may involve computational complexity in designing flexible yet practical service plans. 
5. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper may involve social and information networks in terms of designing service plans that are attractive to both ISPs and subscribers.
